SQL Injection Vulnerability in WHERE Clause Allowing Retrieval of Hidden Data
 Objective
Identify and exploit a SQL Injection vulnerability in the product category filter to access hidden products.
Discovery
The category parameter was tested with a single quote (`'`). The application's behavior indicated that user input was being processed directly in the SQL query, suggesting a possible SQL Injection vulnerability.
Exploitation
he following payload was injected into the category parameter:
' OR 1=1--
This modified the query logic, causing the condition to always evaluate as true and bypassing the `released = 1` restriction.
Result
The application displayed all products, including unreleased products, confirming successful SQL Injection.

